      "csl:lineNumber": 271472,
      "csl:pageColumn": "3-0167",
      "rdf:value": "<L>28050<pc>3-0167<k1>jri<k2>jri<h>1\n1. {#jri#}¦, {#jra/yati = gatikarman#}\n<ls>NAIGH. 2,14.</ls> {%überwältigen%}\n<ls>DHĀTUP. 22,49.</ls>\n<div n=\"p\">— {#upa#} {%sich ausbreiten zu%}(?): {#jigA\\dupa^ jrayati\\ gora^pI\\cya^M pa\\daM yada^sya ma\\tuTA\\ ajI^janan#}\n<ls>ṚV. 9,71,5.</ls>\n<div n=\"p\">— {#pari#} <ab>s.</ab> {#parijri#} .\n<LEND>"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Ajri#record-pwk",
      "@type": "csl:SourceRecord",
      "dct:source": "Boehtlingk PWK",
      "csl:dictionary": "pwk",
      "csl:recordNumber": "43624",
      "csl:lineNumber": 177855,
      "csl:pageColumn": "2-279-c",
      "rdf:value": "<L>43624<pc>2-279-c<k1>jri<k2>jri<h>1\n<hom>1.</hom> √{#jri#}¦, {#jra/yati#}\n<div n=\"1\">— 1〉 *{#gatikarman#}.\n<div n=\"1\">— 2〉 *{#aBiBave#}.\n<div n=\"p\">— Mit {#upa#} {%hingehen zu%} (<ab>Acc.</ab>).\n<div n=\"p\">— Mit {#pari#} in {#parijri/#}.\n<LEND>"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Ajri#record-ap90",
      "@type": "csl:SourceRecord",
      "dct:source": "Apte 1890",
      "csl:dictionary": "ap90",
      "csl:recordNumber": "14117",
      "csl:lineNumber": 121194,
      "csl:pageColumn": "0520-b",
      "rdf:value": "<L>14117<pc>0520-b<k1>jri<k2>jri\n{#jri#}¦ {vI.v} {c1c} <ab>P.</ab> ({#jrayati#}) {@1@} To <lbinfo n=\"over+power\"/>\noverpower, conquer. {@--2@} To go. {vII.v} {9}\n{c10c} <ab>P.</ab> ({#jriRAti, jrAyayati#}) To grow old.\n<LEND>"
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Ajri#record-gra",
      "@type": "csl:SourceRecord",
      "dct:source": "Grassmann Wörterbuch zum Rig-Veda",
      "csl:dictionary": "gra",
      "csl:recordNumber": "3603",
      "csl:lineNumber": 23119,
      "csl:pageColumn": "0506",
      "rdf:value": "<L>3603<pc>0506<k1>jri<k2>jri\r\n{@√jri,@}¦ {%gehen, schreiten%} [gatikarma <ls>Naigh. 〔II,14〕</ls>.], wahrscheinlich mit <hom>2.</hom> jar, also weiter mit car zusammenhängend. In Bezug auf die Bedeutungsentwickelung, wie sie in jráyas hervortritt, <ab>vgl.</ab> cirá von car und uru-gāyá.\r\n<div n=\"Pf\">Mit {@upa,@} {%hinzuschreiten%} zu [<ab>A.</ab>].\r\n<div n=\"Pf\">{@pári,@} {%herumlaufen,%} enthalten in parijrí.\r\n<div n=\"H\">Stamm {@jraya:@}\r\n<div n=\"TS\">-ati úpa {783,5} jígāt úpa jrayati gós apīcíam padám.\r\n<div n=\"P\">Mehrstämmiges Particip {@jrayasāná@} [aus den Stämmen jraya und s (von as)] (<ab n=\"siehe\">s.</ab> für sich).\r\n<div n=\"H\">Verbale {@jrí@}\r\n<div n=\"P\">enthalten in uru-jrí und mit pari in pari-jrí.\r\n<LEND>"
    },
